The paper deals with the problem of computing distances between continuous-time Markov chains (CTMCs) and proposes three different algorithmic methodologies to solve it. This involves concepts from logic (bisimilarity), algorithms (iterative, linear program, on-the-fly), and systems (CTMCs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper also involves concepts from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY), which are also possible sub-categories.
